Information gathered by Connecting Africa shows that, in early February 2020, “there are 24 operators in 18 African countries that are evaluating/testing/trialling/deploying 5G” and of those operators, eight “have deployed 5G into pre-commercial or commercial networks”.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .